	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Hamtaro126 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">Fatboy wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">What about GBDK, is that just for programming in C. Know if it's any good? Thanks</div><br /><br />GBDK has never been updated since 2008, but there is Z88DK for C programs, If there is no GB/C Setup for Z88DK, you may build one for it.</div>
<br />There's also SDCC, which has GB-Z80 support. But I don't know if it comes with any libraries for the GB. It produces better code than Z88DK though, at least when I compared them for the Z80 back in february/march.

		

