		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've got another question, and I think the answer is easy but I couldn't find any help through google.
<br />
<br />Once I've written my program and saved it as a .asm file how do I make a .gbc rom image?
<br />
<br /><a href="http://www.smspower.org/maxim/HowToProgram/SettingItUp" class="postlink">http://www.smspower.org/maxim/HowToProgram/SettingItUp</a>
<br />This link shows how to set up context to use F9 to compile .sms image files. But he uses a batch file that he wrote himself and it only works to create master systems roms. 
<br />
<br />Anybody know of anything like this for the gameboy?
<br />Thanks.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
